Should we report it to the police?

539
00:45:34,565 --> 00:45:35,732
No?

540
00:45:37,234 --> 00:45:39,695
What if we tell the family…

541
00:45:41,029 --> 00:45:42,281
Right, no.

542
00:45:43,157 --> 00:45:44,491
I mean,

543
00:45:44,575 --> 00:45:49,121
if she really did have an affair,
her husband would probably hate her.

544
00:45:49,621 --> 00:45:51,415
Jeez, what do we do?

545
00:45:52,916 --> 00:45:54,543
What should we do?

546
00:45:58,422 --> 00:46:01,925
HENRY'S GRANDMOTHER

547
00:46:02,801 --> 00:46:03,802
Answer it.

548
00:46:08,348 --> 00:46:09,475
Hello?

549
00:46:10,809 --> 00:46:12,519
It's been a while, Dong-seok's mom.

550
00:46:13,562 --> 00:46:14,605
Yes.

551
00:46:14,688 --> 00:46:16,273
How have you been?

552
00:46:16,899 --> 00:46:18,484
I called because this time,

553
00:46:19,067 --> 00:46:22,321
Henry won't stop pestering
me to invite Dong-seok.

554
00:46:22,404 --> 00:46:25,574
Does Dong-seok miss Henry too?

555
00:46:27,117 --> 00:46:29,495
Of course, he does.

556
00:46:30,579 --> 00:46:33,081
Then bring him by sometime soon.

557
00:46:34,166 --> 00:46:35,209
Okay.

558
00:46:37,336 --> 00:46:39,546
By the way, ma'am…

559
00:46:41,465 --> 00:46:43,050
Are you going to tell her?

560
00:46:49,556 --> 00:46:52,643
Thank you for your call.

561
00:46:53,769 --> 00:46:55,270
I'm the grateful one.

562
00:46:55,354 --> 00:46:57,606
Give me a call about the date.

563
00:46:59,316 --> 00:47:00,359
Okay.

564
00:47:00,442 --> 00:47:01,652
Bye.

565
00:47:04,404 --> 00:47:05,531
Gosh.

566
00:47:06,156 --> 00:47:07,991
She doesn't know at all?

567
00:47:08,742 --> 00:47:10,160
No.

568
00:47:10,244 --> 00:47:11,578
Goodness.

569
00:47:13,997 --> 00:47:15,499
Seriously, what do we do?

570
00:47:32,808 --> 00:47:35,644
Kids, this song is called the "Winter."

571
00:47:35,727 --> 00:47:39,856
But I'm not getting any coldness.
Try playing it a little colder.

572
00:47:39,940 --> 00:47:42,651
She's dead but there's
no end to embarrassment.

573
00:47:42,734 --> 00:47:45,862
I know. It's an embarrassment
to the whole neighborhood.

574
00:47:46,947 --> 00:47:49,533
Your little one was
in the same class with her son.

575
00:47:50,158 --> 00:47:52,077
Did you notice anything weird?

576
00:47:53,787 --> 00:47:56,039
Not really, we weren't very close.

577
00:47:56,957 --> 00:47:58,083
Right.

578
00:47:58,166 --> 00:47:59,918
I don't like talking about
other people's business,

579
00:48:00,002 --> 00:48:01,587
but this doesn't feel like it is.

580
00:48:01,670 --> 00:48:03,797
It isn't. It affects the kids.

581
00:48:04,590 --> 00:48:08,719
If she thought it was shameful,
then she shouldn't have done it.

582
00:48:08,802 --> 00:48:11,138
Did you ask my husband for the drugs?

583
00:48:11,221 --> 00:48:13,432
It's because you keep ignoring me.

584
00:48:13,515 --> 00:48:16,768
What scares me the most
is that the kids might hear about it.

585
00:48:16,852 --> 00:48:18,812
That's what scares me the most too.

586
00:48:19,313 --> 00:48:20,939
What are we going to do about this?

587
00:48:21,023 --> 00:48:22,816
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

588
00:48:25,986 --> 00:48:28,113
Now that we've got Song Hae-seon,

589
00:48:28,196 --> 00:48:30,449
it's going to get some attention
from abroad too.

590
00:48:31,158 --> 00:48:35,287
As to its quality, we've got Director Oh,
so there is nothing to worry about.

591
00:48:35,370 --> 00:48:36,997
-Stop it.
-While we're at it,

592
00:48:37,664 --> 00:48:39,207
let's aim for the Cannes Festival.

593
00:48:39,291 --> 00:48:41,168
-Goodbye, Director.
-Bye. Good work today.

594
00:48:41,251 --> 00:48:42,252
-Bye!
-Bye!

595
00:48:42,336 --> 00:48:44,671
-Let's make something great!
-Yes, we got this!

596
00:48:48,300 --> 00:48:49,635
Bye!

597
00:49:12,824 --> 00:49:14,117
So…

598
00:49:15,369 --> 00:49:18,330
you went around saying
you slept with my wife,

599
00:49:19,122 --> 00:49:20,916
but you didn't actually do it?

600
00:49:21,625 --> 00:49:22,793
Well, yes.

601
00:49:23,794 --> 00:49:25,253
I'm sure you know…

602
00:49:27,673 --> 00:49:31,551
about how men bluff when they boast
and how childish it can be.

603
00:49:33,970 --> 00:49:36,181
When Ms. Seo sent me that photo,

604
00:49:36,848 --> 00:49:38,934
I sort of took it as a joke and…

605
00:49:41,812 --> 00:49:46,024
I must've not been thinking
straight at the time. I'm sorry.

606
00:49:47,025 --> 00:49:47,859
And…

607
00:49:49,861 --> 00:49:52,364
My wife stalked you?

608
00:49:55,033 --> 00:49:57,160
Yes, like I've told you.

609
00:50:00,163 --> 00:50:04,960
Then why didn't you mention the photo
during the police investigation?

610
00:50:07,796 --> 00:50:10,799
Right, well…

611
00:50:13,009 --> 00:50:16,888
It was an encrypted message…

612
00:50:35,031 --> 00:50:36,158
Fine.

613
00:50:36,992 --> 00:50:38,827
I'll take your word for it.

614
00:50:42,164 --> 00:50:46,042
But I don't want this issue
taken to the police.

615
00:50:47,252 --> 00:50:51,047
I don't want my wife's personal life
to be disclosed any further.

616
00:50:54,885 --> 00:50:56,845
Please handle this as soon as possible.

617
00:50:58,346 --> 00:51:00,140
If you don't,

618
00:51:00,849 --> 00:51:04,561
you'll also suffer consequences.

619
00:51:05,937 --> 00:51:06,938
Okay.

620
00:51:33,924 --> 00:51:35,884
-Geon-u…
-Don't talk to me.

621
00:51:38,470 --> 00:51:39,763
Damn it!

622
00:52:09,459 --> 00:52:11,002
A CLUB FOR ENLIGHTENED SANGWE MOMS

623
00:52:13,255 --> 00:52:14,756
CHEERS FOR SANGKEMO AND
PROTECTORS OF THE ENVIRONMENT!

624
00:52:29,187 --> 00:52:31,898
Leave my husband alone.

625
00:52:33,400 --> 00:52:36,736
