630
00:53:38,173 --> 00:53:39,299
Let's go in.

631
00:53:39,382 --> 00:53:40,592
Hello.

632
00:53:40,675 --> 00:53:42,135
-Oh, you're here early.
-Ji-hu.

633
00:53:42,218 --> 00:53:43,303
Have some of this.

634
00:53:43,845 --> 00:53:45,597
-Ju-hyeok, have you been practicing?
-Ji-hye, are things going well?

635
00:53:45,680 --> 00:53:46,765
You must be hungry.

636
00:53:56,858 --> 00:54:00,236
-Kids, you must be hungry.
-Here. Have some coffee too.

637
00:54:01,571 --> 00:54:02,906
Are you nervous?

638
00:54:02,989 --> 00:54:04,074
-I'm okay.
-You are?

639
00:54:04,616 --> 00:54:05,784
Just a minute.

640
00:54:07,744 --> 00:54:08,787
You must be hungry.

641
00:54:08,870 --> 00:54:09,871
ORCHESTRA PERFORMANCE
WITH SANGWE ELEMENTARY

642
00:54:09,955 --> 00:54:11,665
This is so annoying.

643
00:54:11,748 --> 00:54:15,126
Why do they make the younger kids come
when it's the older kids performing?

644
00:54:16,086 --> 00:54:18,254
I don't even like it when adults play.

645
00:54:18,338 --> 00:54:20,757
Why do I have to listen to kids?

646
00:54:21,925 --> 00:54:23,593
Jeez.

647
00:54:24,719 --> 00:54:27,472
I can't thank you all enough
for lending me an ear last time.

648
00:54:27,555 --> 00:54:29,349
It really warmed my heart.

649
00:54:29,432 --> 00:54:30,684
-Guys.
-Yes?

650
00:54:30,767 --> 00:54:32,769
-Go get stamps.
-Okay.

651
00:54:32,852 --> 00:54:34,354
Hi.

652
00:54:34,437 --> 00:54:35,355
Bye.

653
00:54:37,774 --> 00:54:39,150
Thank you.

654
00:54:39,859 --> 00:54:40,902
Right?

655
00:54:40,986 --> 00:54:43,613
I'm worried that they're nervous.

656
00:54:49,995 --> 00:54:50,912
It's Byeon Chun-hui.

657
00:54:52,247 --> 00:54:53,373
Right.

658
00:54:53,456 --> 00:54:55,166
Her son is also playing today, right?

659
00:54:57,210 --> 00:54:59,045
SANGWE ELEMENTARY SCHOOL ORCHESTRA

660
00:54:59,129 --> 00:55:01,715
Who cares about the performance?

661
00:55:01,798 --> 00:55:02,716
VIOLIN SOLO: KIM YEONG-BIN

662
00:55:02,799 --> 00:55:04,342
He's playing the solo piece today?

663
00:55:04,843 --> 00:55:06,302
He must be really good.

664
00:55:08,388 --> 00:55:11,182
Eun-pyo. What's she like
when you cross paths with her?

665
00:55:11,266 --> 00:55:13,184
Does she give you the cold shoulder too?

666
00:55:14,227 --> 00:55:15,478
I don't know.

667
00:55:15,562 --> 00:55:17,647
We don't really see each other.

668
00:55:18,565 --> 00:55:20,233
Mom, I got the stamp.

669
00:55:21,443 --> 00:55:22,277
Good job.

670
00:55:22,360 --> 00:55:23,737
-Let's go.
-Let's go.

671
00:55:23,820 --> 00:55:25,113
Let's go in.

672
00:55:42,839 --> 00:55:44,257
There's a seat.

673
00:55:44,340 --> 00:55:45,592
Guys, come on.

674
00:55:45,675 --> 00:55:47,510
-Follow me.
-Hello.

675
00:55:48,094 --> 00:55:49,345
-Hello.
-Hello.

676
00:55:49,429 --> 00:55:51,473
-You're here.
-Hello.

677
00:55:51,556 --> 00:55:54,392
-Hello.
-Hello.

678
00:55:55,393 --> 00:55:58,229
Dong-seok's mom, long time no see.

679
00:55:58,313 --> 00:56:00,398
-How've you been?
-Good. How've you been?

680
00:56:00,940 --> 00:56:05,403
Your skin is glowing.
She must be aging backward.

681
00:56:05,487 --> 00:56:07,655
Oh, come on.

682
00:56:07,739 --> 00:56:09,532
It must be a product she uses.

683
00:56:13,495 --> 00:56:16,414
You've heard about the thing, right?

684
00:56:17,540 --> 00:56:18,374
About what?

685
00:56:20,668 --> 00:56:24,964
Jul-pin's dad is a famous director.

686
00:56:25,673 --> 00:56:26,758
Right?

687
00:56:27,467 --> 00:56:28,384
The photo…

688
00:56:30,303 --> 00:56:31,137
The photo.

689
00:56:31,805 --> 00:56:34,808
Henry's mother sent it
to seduce Jul-pin's dad.

690
00:56:34,891 --> 00:56:36,476
She was a stalker.

691
00:56:36,559 --> 00:56:37,769
Goodness.

692
00:56:37,852 --> 00:56:39,395
Where did you hear that?

693
00:56:39,479 --> 00:56:41,523
-That scared me.
-You're here.

694
00:56:43,233 --> 00:56:47,570
Jul-pin's mom was crying at Enigma

695
00:56:47,654 --> 00:56:50,615
about how her family is in trouble
because of that crazy woman.

696
00:56:50,698 --> 00:56:51,950
It's okay.

697
00:56:52,450 --> 00:56:54,536
I'm really okay.

698
00:56:54,619 --> 00:56:55,954
It's just…

699
00:56:56,037 --> 00:57:00,500
I've worked so hard for so long
to eradicate discrimination against women.

700
00:57:00,583 --> 00:57:03,294
But now that something
like this has happened…

701
00:57:03,962 --> 00:57:05,421
I can't believe it.

702
00:57:07,507 --> 00:57:10,677
It's heartbreaking that his name
is being slandered like this.

703
00:57:10,760 --> 00:57:13,388
-Especially at such an important moment.
-Oh, no.

704
00:57:13,471 --> 00:57:17,142
I can't believe something
like this is happening to me.

705
00:57:17,809 --> 00:57:19,727
I just can't believe all this.

706
00:57:19,811 --> 00:57:22,605
Goodness. You must feel terrible.

707
00:57:23,314 --> 00:57:25,650
I thought it was just
something people talked about.

708
00:57:25,733 --> 00:57:28,319
I never thought I'd be the victim…

709
00:57:28,403 --> 00:57:32,824
So she's saying Henry's mother took
the photo and sent it herself, right?

710
00:57:34,159 --> 00:57:35,702
I guess so.

711
00:57:36,411 --> 00:57:38,413
But why would she?

712
00:57:40,623 --> 00:57:42,208
To seduce him.

713
00:57:43,960 --> 00:57:47,630
It doesn't make sense.
Why would she take and send it herself?

714
00:57:47,714 --> 00:57:49,841
Yun-ju, keep an eye
on Dong-seok for a minute.

715
00:57:50,592 --> 00:57:51,926
Eun-pyo, where are you going?

716
00:57:52,469 --> 00:57:54,345
-No, not yet.
-Oh, please.

717
00:57:54,429 --> 00:57:56,055
As a leader of Sangwe Moms…

718
00:57:56,139 --> 00:57:58,183
All right. Enjoy the show.

719
00:57:58,266 --> 00:57:59,350
-Bye.
-See you later.

720
00:57:59,434 --> 00:58:00,435
-Bye.
-Bye.

721
00:58:01,895 --> 00:58:03,188
We need to talk.

722
00:58:05,023 --> 00:58:07,108
About what?

723
00:58:07,192 --> 00:58:08,568
Are you kidding me?

724
00:58:08,651 --> 00:58:11,446
You told me not to tell anyone
and even threatened me.

725
00:58:11,529 --> 00:58:13,740
Why are you going around telling people?

726
00:58:16,618 --> 00:58:19,996
I don't understand
what you're talking about.

727
00:58:20,079 --> 00:58:22,373
What are you trying to do to the deceased?

728
00:58:40,141 --> 00:58:43,019
The performance is about to start.

729
00:58:43,102 --> 00:58:47,106
May everyone in the hall please be seated.

730
00:58:49,943 --> 00:58:51,027
Let's talk outside.

731
00:59:17,470 --> 00:59:19,180
What's going on?

732
00:59:19,264 --> 00:59:20,723
Are they fighting?

733
00:59:20,807 --> 00:59:23,434
About what? What grade moms?

734
00:59:23,518 --> 00:59:26,646
That pill in Sangkemo
and a first grader's mom.

735
00:59:26,729 --> 00:59:27,772
What happened?

736
00:59:27,855 --> 00:59:30,149
It must be about that rumor.

737
00:59:30,233 --> 00:59:31,943
Do you think it'll get physical?

738
00:59:32,026 --> 00:59:34,112
I'd rather see them than the performance.

739
00:59:43,454 --> 00:59:44,664
It's cowardly.

740
00:59:45,331 --> 00:59:49,085
It's cowardly to do this to the deceased
who can't speak up just to save your neck.

741
00:59:51,170 --> 00:59:54,132
I never put any stock
in that recording anyway.

742
00:59:54,716 --> 00:59:58,052
I stayed quiet because I didn't think
you'd go this far as a mother.

743
00:59:58,803 --> 01:00:00,805
But you're crossing the line!

744
01:00:00,888 --> 01:00:02,390
It's despicable!

745
01:00:13,943 --> 01:00:15,445
There's your brother.

746
01:02:01,759 --> 01:02:02,677
Who is it?

747
01:02:10,518 --> 01:02:11,644
Yes.

748
01:02:12,437 --> 01:02:13,646
How admirable of you.

749
01:02:14,397 --> 01:02:18,568
Resolutely standing up
for your dead friend.

750
01:02:18,651 --> 01:02:20,194
How touching.

751
01:02:21,863 --> 01:02:25,158
Actually, I've felt this
since a while back.

752
01:02:25,742 --> 01:02:29,328
You're quite a hypocrite yourself.

753
01:02:30,872 --> 01:02:31,914
In fact,

754
01:02:32,582 --> 01:02:35,626
there's this one thing I didn't tell you.

755
01:02:36,294 --> 01:02:38,004
And I wonder

756
01:02:38,087 --> 01:02:42,759
if your hypocrisy
will last when you hear it.

757
01:02:43,384 --> 01:02:44,594
Be honest.

758
01:02:45,470 --> 01:02:46,971
Weren't you angry

759
01:02:47,054 --> 01:02:48,806
that she took your boyfriend?

760
01:02:51,225 --> 01:02:54,312
The thing is, Henry's mother said

761
01:02:54,395 --> 01:02:57,982
she took him from you on purpose.

762
01:03:00,610 --> 01:03:03,863
I took him from her on purpose.

763
01:03:05,031 --> 01:03:06,991
I knew they were dating.

764
01:03:07,825 --> 01:03:10,953
I watched them for a long time in secret.

765
01:03:11,037 --> 01:03:14,999
-Kiss!
-Kiss!

766
01:03:15,082 --> 01:03:17,710
And then I decided on the D-Day.

767
01:03:18,711 --> 01:03:20,963
I wanted to crush Eun-pyo
into a miserable pulp

768
01:03:21,672 --> 01:03:23,674
when she was at the height of her glory.

769
01:03:26,260 --> 01:03:27,428
Eun-pyo.

770
01:03:31,557 --> 01:03:32,517
Eun-pyo.

771
01:03:32,600 --> 01:03:36,312
It didn't matter who the guy was.

772
01:03:36,979 --> 01:03:38,272
What mattered…

773
01:03:39,065 --> 01:03:42,819
was showing Eun-pyo
that what she thought of as hers

774
01:03:42,902 --> 01:03:46,823
might not actually be hers.

775
01:03:46,906 --> 01:03:47,740
You're lying!

776
01:03:49,575 --> 01:03:51,160
You're lying.

777
01:03:51,244 --> 01:03:52,745
It can't be.

778
01:03:53,412 --> 01:03:55,748
Jin-ha wouldn't have done that to me.

779
01:03:56,499 --> 01:03:57,834
She wouldn't have!

780
01:05:32,720 --> 01:05:34,889
I'm not going to live with you anymore,
